An Act relative to school mascot name changes.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Chapter 71 of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after section 37R the
2 following section:-
3 Section 37S. (a) For the purposes of this section “school branding” shall mean any name,
4 symbol or image used by a school as a mascot, nickname, logo, letterhead, team name, slogan,
5 motto or other identifier.
6 (b) Prior to any change in school branding where the current school branding references
7 any person, group of persons, organization, race, creed, color, national origin, sexual orientation
8 or gender identity, the school committee for the school district that the school belongs to shall
9 hold a hearing on the proposed school branding change. The hearing shall be open to the public
10 and at least 1 representative of the group, organization or identity referenced in the school
